est Ham United]] ([[FA Premier League 2002\u201303#League table|2002\u201303]])<ref name=autogenerated5 />\n* Fewest points in a season while avoiding relegation: 34, [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] ([[FA Premier League 2004\u201305#League table|2004\u201305]])<ref name=autogenerated5/>\n*Most points in a season by a team promoted in the previous season:\n** 42 games: 77, [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] ([[1993\u201394 FA Premier League#League table|1993\u201394]]) and [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] ([[1994\u201395 FA Premier League#League table|1994\u201395]]){{citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n** 38 games: 66, [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] ([[2000\u201301 FA Premier League#League table|2000\u201301]])<ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Plant |title=The 6 Highest Finishes Achieved by Sides Promoted to the Premier League |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/4565698-the-6-highest-finishes-achieved-by-sides-promoted-to-the-premier-league |website=90min.com |accessdate=15 May 2019 |date=13 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Wins===\n*Most wins in total: 659, [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/clubs/wins?co=1&se=-1&co=-1?se=-1|website=premierleague.com|accessdate=14 May 2018|title=Premier League Club Stats}}</ref>\n*Most wins in a season: 32, [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] ([[2017\u201318 Premier League#League table|2017\u201318]], [[2018\u201319 Premier League|2018\u201319]])<ref>{{cite web |first=Haran |last=Naresh |title=Manchester City 2018/19 Review: End of Season Report Card for the Citizens |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/6367974-manchester-city-2018-19-review-end-of-season-report-card-for-the-citizens |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=15 May 2019 |date=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n*Most home wins in a season: 18<ref name=\"PLrecords\">{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/records |title=Premier League Records |website=premierleague.com |a