-ever-premier-league-point-totals-in-the-noughties|title=5 Lowest Ever Premier League Point Totals (In The Noughties)|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Fewest home points in a season: 7, [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] ([[2005\u201306 FA Premier League#Results|2005\u201306]])<ref name=\"Independent\"/>\n* Fewest away points in a season: 3, [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] ([[2007\u201308 Premier League#Results|2007\u201308]])<ref name=\"Independent\"/>\n* Most points in a season without winning the league: 97, [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] ([[2018\u201319 Premier League#League table|2018\u201319]])<ref name=\"records2018/19\">{{cite web |first=Naveen |last=Joseph |title=5 Premier League records that were broken this season |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/1097190/5-premier-league-records-that-were-broken-this-season/ |website=FOX Sports Asia |accessdate=14 May 2019 |date=13 May 2019}}</ref>\n* Fewest points in a season while winning the league: 75, [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] ([[FA Premier League 1996\u201397#League table|1996\u201397]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitrowz.com/2014/07/15/what-does-it-take-to-win-the-premier-league|title=hitrowz.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150422182519/http://hitrowz.com/2014/07/15/what-does-it-take-to-win-the-premier-league|archivedate=22 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Most points in a season while being relegated:\n** 42 games: 49, [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] ([[FA Premier League 1992\u201393#League table|1992\u201393]])<ref name=autogenerated5>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/premier-league/11469196/Premier-League-relegation-battle-how-many-points-do-you-need-to-stay-up.html|title=Premier League relegation battle \u2013 how many points do you need to stay up?|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n** 38 games: 42, [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] ([[FA Premier League 2002\u201303#League table|