: 7\n**[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] 8\u20130 [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] (23 December 2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/20745787|title=Chelsea 8\u20130 Aston Villa|first=Owen|last=Phillips|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n**[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] 7\u20130 [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] (2 November 2013)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/24681355|title=Manchester City 7\u20130 Norwich City|first=Gary|last=Rose|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n**[[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] 8\u20130 [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] (18 October 2014)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29580147|title=Southampton 8\u20130 Sunderland|first=Luke|last=Reddy|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==All-time Premier League table==\nThe all-time Premier League table is a cumulative record of all match results, points and goals of every team that has played in the Premier League since its inception in 1992. The table that follows is accurate as of the end of the [[2018\u201319 Premier League|2018\u201319]] season. Teams in '''bold''' are part of the [[2019\u201320 Premier League]]. Numbers in '''bold''' are the record (highest either positive or negative) numbers in each column.<ref name=\"alltimetable\"/>\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT UPDATE UNTIL END OF SEASON as this causes problems in updating at the end of each season when each part of the table should be updated in full. Whilst the table is by points total, the number of Premierships won is also shown. Please do not remove without seeing comment this article's talk page. Thank you.-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Pos.\n!Club\n!Seasons\n!Pld\n!Win\n!Draw\n!Loss\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Pts\n!1st\n!2nd\n!3rd\n!4th\n!Relegated\n!Best<br />Pos.\n|- style=\"background:#ace1af\"\n|1||align=left|'''[[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]'''\n|'''27'''||'''1,038'''||'''648'''||224||166||'''1,989'''||929||'''1,060'''||'''2,168'''||'''13'''||'''6'''|